The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, January 26, 2004 				 Blaze arrests
																								Chennai, Jan. 25: Four persons were arrested today in connection with the marriage hall blaze in Srirangam that claimed 67 lives, reports our special correspondent. 																								Among those held were the manager of the marriage hall, the pandal contractor and the electrician, sources said. 																								George, IG, central zone, ruled out sabotage and placed his suspicion on the powerful flashbulb used by the videographer. After the screening of a videotape seized from the hall, he said it was clear that the 1,000-watt flashbulb was a major cause behind the blaze. Videographer Dharmaraj, who was covering the function, got admitted to a private hospital in Tiruchirapally yesterday, the sources said. 
